y from the perspective of the library and information sciences. It includes essays on strategies for practical implementation of support for information literacy in schools, universities, and research facilities. A particular focus is placed on designing such programs to promote learning through calculated spatial and technical infrastructures and didactically effective planning.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aInformation literacyxStudy and teaching. 0aInformation literacy. 4aInformation literacy. 4aInformationskompetenz. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Library & Information Science / General.2bisacsh1 aStraub, Martina1 aSühl-Strohmenger, Wilfried, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Library and Information Science 2016z9783110485240oZDB-23-DGB0 cEPUBz97831104034280 cprintz978311040329940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311040336740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110403367423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110403367.jpg  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LB  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGBb2016  aZDB-23-DGGb2016